meta {
  name: 02 Wait for Ready
  type: http
  seq: 2
}

get {
  url: https://{{instanceId}}.{{proxyDomain}}/v1/health
  body: none
  auth: none
}

headers {
  Authorization: Bearer {{token}}
}

tests {
  test("agent is up", function () {
    expect(res.status).to.equal(200);
    expect(res.body.ok).to.equal(true);
  });
}

docs {
  The first request that talks to the instance directly instead of api.agent37.com: it hits the
  instance's own URL on the public edge (https://{instanceId}.agent37.app), authenticated with
  the same sk_live_ key.

  01 Create Instance returns once the container is "running", but the agent inside needs a moment
  more to come up. While it is still booting this returns 502 or 503 — click Send again every few
  seconds until you get 200 with ok: true. On a cold host that can take a minute or two. Then move
  on to 03 Send Message.
}
